cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper deals with natural language processing and specifically with discourse parsing, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper proposes neural network models for implicit discourse relation classification, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The models are based on feedforward and long-short term memory architecture, which are common techniques in machine learning and deep learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves tuning of hyperparameters, which is a common task in neural network optimization (cs.NE). Finally, the paper deals with cross-linguistic discourse parsing, which involves information retrieval and information extraction (cs.IR).
